    "recap_headline": "College of Charleston",
    "recap_text": "SPARTANBURG, S.C. \u2013\nCollege of Charleston baseball lost to Wofford, 13-9, Wednesday evening at Russell C. King Field.\nDown 7-0, Charleston fought back, eventually leveling the contest at nine before surrendering four runs in the seventh.\nCRITICAL POINTS AGAINST WOFFORD:\nWofford came out swinging and paired with Charleston defensive miscues, held a 7-0 advantage after two.\nCofC's comeback efforts began in the third, scoring five in the frame backed behind sophomore\nAlex LaCoste's\ngrand slam.\nDown 9-6, redshirt junior\nBraeden Smith's\ntwo-run shot in the fifth put the Cougars within one.\nLaCoste came up clutch again the very next inning, singling up the middle to plate sophomore\nLandon Penfield\n.\nWofford regained the lead for good in the seventh, scoring four runs to break the tie.\nLaCoste went 2-for-4 in the game with a walk and career-best five RBI.\nPenfield and graduate\nReece Holbrook\nalso collected multi-hit efforts in the loss.\nOF NOTE:\nCharleston is now 41-13 against Wofford and 19-7 as the road team.\nCofC has slugged multiple home runs for the second straight game and third time this year.\nLaCoste hit the 66th grand slam in program history, becoming the 51st player to do so.\nThe Cougars have hit multiple grand slams in the same season 14 times.\nFreshman\nAustin Wiegandt\nappeared in his second ballgame on the mound, striking out a pair in a scoreless eighth.\nUP NEXT:\nCharleston hosts Stony Brook for a three-game conference series March 13-15 at Patriots Point. First pitch in the opener is set for 6 p.m.\nFor complete coverage of Charleston baseball, follow us X (@CofCBaseball) and Instagram (@CofC_Baseball)."
